-- Adidas shares up on report hedge funds eye stake 
-- By Thomas Atkins
-- Wed Sep 17, 2014 04:35AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, Sept 17 (Reuters) - Shares in sportwearmaker Adidas <ADSGn.DE> rose 1.7 percent to the top of the German blue-chip DAX index <.GDAXI> on Wednesday following a magazine report saying that hedge funds were considering purchasing stake in the company.

Adidas was not immediately available for comment on the summary of a report to appear in Germany's manager magazin, which cited unnamed sources. The hedge funds include Third Point, run by Daniel Loeb, Knight Vinke, run by Eric Knight, and TCI, run by Chris Hohn, the magazine said. Adidas shares were up 1.4 percent to 59.55 euros by 0832 GMT, leading a 0.35 percent rise in the DAX.